  "The terms and conditions written in the fine print": "",
  "The loan term is the duration over which the loan must be repaid. Common terms include 15 or 30 years for mortgages, 3-7 years for auto loans, and 10-25 years for student loans. Longer terms mean lower payments but more total interest.": "",
  "What is 'refinancing' a loan?": "",
