  "DTI is 50%; he exceeds the threshold": "",
  "DTI is 10.8%; yes, he qualifies easily with room for a mortgage payment": "",
  "DTI is 43%; he is at the maximum threshold": "",
  "Current DTI = ($300 + $200 + $150) / $6,000 = $650 / $6,000 = 10.8%. Since 43% of $6,000 is $2,580, Kevin could add up to $1,930 in mortgage payments ($2,580 - $650) and still remain under the 43% threshold.": "",
  "Sarah is comparing two auto loans for a $25,000 car. Loan A: 4.5% for 48 months (payment: $570). Loan B: 3.9% for 72 months (payment: $390). Which loan costs less in total interest?": "",
